  "prompt": "Which is a suitable solar panel installation provider in La Habra, California CA?",
  "response": "When looking for a suitable solar panel installation provider in La Habra, California, it's important to choose a reputable company with strong reviews, certifications, and experience. Here are some well-regarded solar installation providers in the area:\n\n### 1. **SunPower by Stellar Solar**\n   - **Why Choose Them:** SunPower is a top-tier solar panel manufacturer, and Stellar Solar is a trusted local installer. They offer high-efficiency solar panels and comprehensive services.\n   - **Certifications:** NABCEP (North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners) certified.\n   - **Website:** [www.stellarsolar.net](https://www.stellarsolar.net)\n\n### 2. **SolarTech Universal**\n   - **Why Choose Them:** Known for their customer service and quality installations, SolarTech Universal offers customized solar solutions.\n   - **Certifications:** NABCEP certified and BBB accredited.\n   - **Website:** [www.solartechuniversal.com](https://www.solartechuniversal.com)\n\n### 3. **Semper Solaris**\n   - **Why Choose Them:** Semper Solaris is a veteran-owned company offering solar, roofing, and battery storage solutions. They have a strong reputation in Southern California.\n   - **Certifications:** NABCEP certified and BBB accredited.\n   - **Website:** [www.sempersolaris.com](https://www.sempersolaris.com)\n\n### 4. **Baker Electric Sun Energy**\n   - **Why Choose Them:** Baker Electric has been serving Southern California for decades and offers high-quality solar installations and energy storage solutions.\n   - **Certifications:** NABCEP certified and BBB accredited.\n   - **Website:** [www.bakerelectricsun.com](https://www.bakerelectricsun.com)\n\n### 5. **La Habra Solar Solutions**\n   - **Why Choose Them:** A local provider specializing in residential and commercial solar installations. They offer personalized service and competitive pricing.\n   - **Website:** [www.lahabrasolar.com](https://www.lahabrasolar.com)\n\n### Tips for Choosing a Provider:\n- **Check Reviews:** Look for customer reviews on platforms like Google, Yelp, and the Better Business Bureau (BBB).\n- **Get Multiple Quotes:** Compare quotes from at least three providers to ensure competitive pricing and service offerings.\n- **Verify Certifications:** Ensure the company is NABCEP certified and has proper licensing and insurance.\n- **Warranty and Maintenance:** Inquire about warranties on equipment and workmanship, as well as maintenance services.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, consider reaching out directly to these providers or consulting online directories like EnergySage or SolarReviews.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
